.TH "TEMPORAL.PLAINDATE.UNTIL" "3JS" "December 8, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
Temporal.PlainDate.until \- Temporal.PlainDate.prototype.until()
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]until()\f[B]\f[R] method of \f[CR]Temporal.PlainDate\f[R]
instances returns a new \f[CR]Temporal.Duration\f[R] object representing
the duration from this date to another date (in a form convertible by
\f[CR]Temporal.PlainDate.from()\f[R]).
The duration is positive if the other date is after this date, and
negative if before.
.PP
This method does \f[CR]other \- this\f[R].
To do \f[CR]this \- other\f[R], use the \f[CR]since()\f[R] method.
.SH SYNTAX
.IP
.EX
until(other)
until(other, options)
.EE
.SS Parameters
.TP
\f[B]other\f[R]
A string, an object, or a \f[CR]Temporal.PlainDate\f[R] instance
representing a date to subtract this date from.
It is converted to a \f[CR]Temporal.PlainDate\f[R] object using the same
algorithm as \f[CR]Temporal.PlainDate.from()\f[R].
It must have the same calendar as \f[CR]this\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]options\f[R] \f[I](optional)\f[R]
The same options as \f[CR]since()\f[R].
.SS Return value
A new \f[CR]Temporal.Duration\f[R] object representing the duration from
this date \f[I]until\f[R] \f[CR]other\f[R].
The duration is positive if \f[CR]other\f[R] is after this date, and
negative if before.
.SS Exceptions
.TP
\f[B]RangeError\f[R]
Thrown in one of the following cases:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]other\f[R] has a different calendar than \f[CR]this\f[R].
.IP \(bu 2
Any of the options is invalid.
.RE
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS Using until()
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] launch = Temporal.PlainDate.from(\(dq2035\-01\-01\(dq);
\f[B]const\f[R] now = Temporal.Now.plainDateISO();
\f[B]const\f[R] duration = now.until(launch);
console.log(\(gaIt will be ${duration.toLocaleString(\(dqen\-US\(dq)} until the launch\(ga);
.EE
.PP
For more examples, see \f[CR]since()\f[R].
